{
  "texts": [
    "Each HSRNN consists of multiple recurrent layers with increasing hidden dimensions and a subsampling step between layers.",
    "For each layer, the input sequence is divided into non-overlapping segments defined by a predefined subsampling factor.",
    "Each element within a segment is processed by its own position-specific weight matrix, and the resulting outputs are summed and combined with the recurrent input from the previous hidden state.",
    "The unconstrained model uses the standard tanh activation, while the constrained model replaces it with an offset absolute or offset ReLU activation to maintain non-negative hidden states.",
    "The output sequence of one layer serves as the input to the next."
  ]
}